=head1 DESCRIPTION

The termination policy for the Amazon EBS volume when the task exits.
For more information, see Amazon ECS volume termination policy
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECS/latest/developerguide/ebs-volumes.html#ebs-volume-types).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> DeleteOnTermination => Bool

Indicates whether the volume should be deleted on when the task stops.
If a value of C<true> is specified, Amazon ECS deletes the Amazon EBS
volume on your behalf when the task goes into the C<STOPPED> state. If
no value is specified, the default value is C<true> is used. When set
to C<false>, Amazon ECS leaves the volume in your account.



